king: C (quick correct decisions), A (anticipates dangerous situations), D (solves problems extremely well), B (no explicit decision-making). So C and A.\n\n- Teamwork/communication: C creates positive atmosphere but difficulty communicating ideas and egocentric; B pretentious, wrong tone, grumpy, uncooperative; A unfriendly, show-off, not open to criticism; D loner, moody, hot temper. So C maybe best crew morale despite communication difficulty; B and A have more negative interpersonal; D also negative.\n\n- Professional development: C not willing to further education (negative), B no info, A no info, D no info. So B maybe best.\n\nThus trade-offs: C strongest reliability, calmness, decision-making, crew morale, but communication difficulty and ego may affect crew coordination. B strong reliability, stress handling, technical, but interpersonal tone issues could affect crew. A strong technical and leadership but poor teamwork. D strong problem solving but attitude.\n\nWhich candidate overall best? Likely C, because reliability and calmness are critical for safety, and crew morale is positive. Communication difficulty is a concern but could be mitigated; egocentric may be less severe than show-off or pretentiousness. Also C's willingness to keep crew positive is valuable.\n\nThus I might shift from A to C, aligning with Agent1. However need to consider that C is not willing to further education, which may affect long-term suitability. But long-distance pilot role may not require further education soon; still professional development is a factor.\n\nGiven the evidence, I think C is best overall. So I will update my vote to Candidate C.\n\nConfidence moderate (maybe 55-60%). Uncertainty: severity of communication difficulty and egocentric behavior; impact of lack of further education.\n\nWe should also note that we considered all candidates and weighed trade-offs.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing.\n\nWe need to reference evidence from others: mention that Agent1 highlighted reliability and crew atmosphere, Agent3 highlighted B's strengths, etc.\n\nNow produce final output."}
